Package: pimbayes
Type: Package
Title: Comprehensive tools for Bayesian inference with partially identified models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Seren", "Lee", role = c("aut","cre"), email = "seren.lee@stat.ubc.ca", comment=c(ORCID="0009-0001-3739-5857")), person("Paul", "Gustafson", role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID="0000-0002-2375-5006")))
Maintainer: Seren Lee <seren.lee@stat.ubc.ca>
Description: Diagnose a suspected partially identified model and provide options for the posterior inference with it, such as the importance sampling with transparent reparameterization (ISTP) or non-reversible Parallel tempering: 
  - ISTP algorthm is described in Lee and Gustafson (2024) <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2408.10416>,
  - A usage of non-reversible parallel tempering method is enabled by Pigeson.jl package Surjanovic et al. (2023) <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2308.09769>,
  - Diagnosing a suspected partially identified model is based on approximating the Fisher information matrix introduced in Spall (2005) <doi:10.1198/106186005X78800>.
